				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11740721#post-4431210</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11740721/scp-4322#post-4431210</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 25 Nov 2019 11:24:05 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rokurokubi</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5700026</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have corrected the description in the Info Bar of your article (<a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4322">SCP-4322</a>, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4339">SCP-4339</a>, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3597">SCP-3597</a>, <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4781">SCP-4781</a>). It is necessary to make it work properly. However, when I looked at the editing history after that, I realized the possibility that you intentionally made them not work.</p> <p>This section explains how to delete &quot;Translations:&quot; correctly.</p> <p>1. Move the Info Bar include statement to top of the page source. This is a necessary process.</p> <p>2. Add the following code in <span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">[[module&#32;CSS]]</span>:</p> <blockquote> <p>.translation_block {<br /> display:none;<br /> }</p> </blockquote> <p>3. Now you can remove the display of &quot;Translations:&quot;!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
