				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11740721#post-4247647</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-11740721/scp-4322#post-4247647</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 13 May 2019 15:19:51 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>T Rutherford</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4620432</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I like this. The &quot;End of Death&quot; hub seems to be following a kind of chronology. First, articles dealt with the initial overpopulation and realization, then later articles with the degradation of an aging humanity, then with easing of suffering. Now, we're addressing an End of Death scenario where there are humans who have broken down to the point of being, essentially, just disembodied consciousness. Not only that, you do it in a way that's unexpected, and interesting!</p> <p>+1 for sure.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
